Been to the club or a workout class lately? Then you‚Äôve probably heard ‚ÄúPepas,‚Äù the party anthem that turned Farruko into a crossover star. And guess what? ‚ÄúPepas‚Äù wasn‚Äôt the only hit on the Puerto Rican singer/rapper's acclaimed ‚ÄòLa 167‚Äô album. ‚ÄúLa Toxica‚Äù - especially the remix with Myke Towers and Sech - was a highly successful return to his reggaeton roots. The album's ‚ÄúEl Incomprendido‚Äù plays with the feisty guaracha style, which blends traditional elements of cumbia and regional Mexican with pulsing EDM arrangements. Farruko and his pal DJ Adoni couldn't stop dancing when they hit our Ctrl studios. Farruko kept the energy whirring on ‚ÄúHelic√≥ptero,‚Äù too. No question, both are infectious blasts of energy.

Been to the club or a workout class lately? Then you‚Äôve probably heard ‚ÄúPepas,‚Äù the party anthem that turned Farruko into a crossover star. And guess what? ‚ÄúPepas‚Äù wasn‚Äôt the only hit on the Puerto Rican singer/rapper's acclaimed ‚ÄòLa 167‚Äô album. ‚ÄúLa Toxica‚Äù - especially the remix with Myke Towers and Sech - was a highly successful return to his reggaeton roots. The album's ‚ÄúEl Incomprendido‚Äù plays with the feisty guaracha style, which blends traditional elements of cumbia and regional Mexican with pulsing EDM arrangements. Farruko and his pal DJ Adoni couldn't stop dancing when they hit our Ctrl studios. Farruko kept the energy whirring on ‚ÄúHelic√≥ptero,‚Äù too. No question, both are infectious blasts of energy.
